### 🔵 BOTTLENECK #6: `HonchoClient.ensureWorkspace()` Called Redundantly

**File:** `src/honcho-client.ts:56–73`

```typescript
async peer(peerName: string): Promise<Peer | null> {
  await this.ensureWorkspace();           // ← Called every time
  const getResp = await fetch(...);
  if (getResp.ok) return ...;
  const createResp = await fetch(...);     // ← Workspace likely already exists
}
```

Every `peer()`, `session()`, `addMessages()` call triggers a `fetch` to check workspace existence. This is wasteful — the workspace check should be **memoized per client instance**.

**Fix:**

```typescript
private _workspaceChecked = false;
private _workspaceValid = false;

async ensureWorkspace(): Promise<boolean> {
  if (this._workspaceChecked && this._workspaceValid) return true;
  // ...existing logic...
  if (resp.ok) {
    this._workspaceChecked = true;
    this._workspaceValid = true;
    return true;
  }
  // ... create logic ...
  this._workspaceChecked = true;
  this._workspaceValid = createResp.ok;
  return createResp.ok;
}
```

**Expected improvement:** ~20–30% faster per-peer/per-session operation (eliminates 1 HTTP round-trip per call).

